The paper deals with visual category recognition, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract information from unstructured text sources, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of auxiliary information and transfer learning is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the incorporation of semantic part annotations involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
